</pre><P><b>
12. 	Now answer this question honestly. Did you know before today that national labor unions are using mandatory monthly dues to pay $35 million in political campaign ads and other election activities this year?</b><p><pre>
40%		KNEW
58%		DID NOT KNOW
2%		DON'T KNOW/ REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
13. 	The AFL-CIO has announced that it will spend $35 million in mandatory monthly dues to defeat 75 incumbent Republican Congressman. Approximately $20 million of that amount will be spent on negative political advertising -- all of it targeted to defeat Republican candidates. Do you strongly support, somewhat support, somewhat oppose, or strongly oppose this use of your union dues for this political effort?</b><p><pre>
15%		STRONGLY SUPPORT
16%		SOMEWHAT SUPPORT
31%	TOTAL SUPPORT
21%		SOMEWHAT OPPOSE
41%		STRONGLY OPPOSE
62%	TOTAL OPPOSE
8%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSE
</pre><P><b>
14. 	Did you know before today that you have the right to get a refund for the portion of your mandatory monthly union dues that is spent on political election activities?</b><p><pre>
19%		YES, KNEW
78%		NO, DID NOT KNOW
3%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
15.	Knowing that you have the right to a refund, how likely would you be to request that refund?</b><p><pre>
20%		DEFINITELY
