16%		SOMEWHAT LIKELY
56%	TOTAL LIKELY
29%		SOMEWHAT UNLIKELY
9%		VERY UNLIKELY
38%
6%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>

16.	In general, who represents your views involving union policy and priorities... your local union leadership or your national union leaders?</b><p><pre>
66%		LOCAL LEADERSHIP
21%		NATIONAL LEADERSHIP
13%		DON'T KNOW? REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
17.	And in general, who better represents your views involving candidates, politics and political campaign issues...your local union leadership or your national union leaders?</b><p><pre>
44%		LOCAL LEADERSHIP
32%		NATIONAL LEADERSHIP
24%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
18.	How often do you follow the political views and political advice of your local leadership/National union leaders?</b><p><pre>
5%		ALWAYS
19%		USUALLY
34%		SOMETIMES
24%		RARELY
5%		NEVER
13%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
18a.	How often do you follow the political views and political advice of your local leadership?</b><p><pre>
6%		ALWAYS
22%		USUALLY
38%		SOMETIMES
19%		RARELY
6%		NEVER
10%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
18b.	How often do you follow the political views and political advice of your National union leaders?</b><p><pre>
5%		ALWAYS
17%		USUALLY
30%		SOMETIMES
28%		RARELY
5%		NEVER
15%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
19.	If all you knew about two candidates for Congress was that your local union chapter endorsed one candidate and the national union leadership endorsed another candidate, which would you be more likely to support?</b><p><pre>
41%		LOCAL LEADERSHIP
13%		NATIONAL LEADERSHIP
46%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
20.	Every year, unions collect millions of dollars in member dues. Currently they do not have to disclose to you how they spend your money. Would you strongly support, somewhat support, somewhat oppose, or strongly oppose making union leaders disclose exactly how they spend your dues?</b><p><pre>
67%		STRONGLY SUPPORT
17%		SOMEWHAT SUPPORT
84%	TOTAL SUPPORT
4%		SOMEWHAT OPPOSE
5%		STRONGLY OPPOSE
9%	TOTAL OPPOSE
7%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
Now I am going to read you a series of proposals and I want you to tell me whether you strongly support, somewhat support, somewhat oppose or strongly oppose each proposal.</b><p><pre></pre><P><b>

21.	Welfare reform that requires recipients to work and limits the length of time they can collect welfare checks.</b><p><pre>
63%		STRONGLY SUPPORT
24%		SOMEWHAT SUPPORT
87%	TOTAL SUPPORT
3%		SOMEWHAT OPPOSE
4%		STRONGLY OPPOSE
7%	TOTAL OPPOSE
7%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
22.	A balanced budget amendment that constitutionally requires Congress to balance the budget each year.</b><p><pre>
58%		STRONGLY SUPPORT
24%		SOMEWHAT SUPPORT
82%	TOTAL SUPPORT
6%		SOMEWHAT OPPOSE
5%		STRONGLY OPPOSE
11%	TOTAL OPPOSE
7%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
23.	Tax reductions that include a $500 per child tax credit?</b><p><pre>
47%		STRONGLY SUPPORT
31%		SOMEWHAT SUPPORT
78%	TOTAL SUPPORT
6%		SOMEWHAT OPPOSE
7%		STRONGLY OPPOSE
13%	TOTAL OPPOSE
9%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
Getting into broader issues...
<P>
24.	If you knew that national unions opposed all three of these measures, and planned to spend millions of dollars in your mandatory union dues to campaign against them, how likely would you be to request a refund of the portion of your dues that went to political activities?</b><p><pre>
44%		VERY LIKELY
15%		SOMEWHAT LIKELY
59%	TOTAL LIKELY
13%		SOMEWHAT UNLIKELY
16%		VERY UNLIKELY
29%	TOTAL UNLIKELY
13%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
25.	And if Congress/Republicans in Congress were to produce a balanced budget, would that be a good thing or a bad thing for working families?</b><p><pre>
65%		GOOD FOR FAMILIES
13%		BAD FOR FAMILIES
22%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
25a.	And if Congress were to produce a balanced budget, would that be a good thing or a bad thing for working families?</b><p><pre>
69%		GOOD FOR FAMILIES
11%		BAD FOR FAMILIES
20%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
25b.	And if Republicans in Congress were to produce a balanced budget, would that be a good thing or bad thing for working families?</b><p><pre>
61%		GOOD FOR FAMILIES
15%		BAD FOR FAMILIES
24%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
26.	What is your age, please? (READ CATAGORIES)</b><p><pre>
6%		18-29
22%		30-39
28%		40-49
22%		50-59
18%		60+
3%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
27.	What is the highest level of education you completed?</b><p><pre>
5%		SOME HIGH SCHOOL OR LESS
32%		COMPLETED HIGH SCHOOL
34%		VOCATIONAL SCHOOL OR SOME COLLEGE
17%		COLLEGE GRADUATE
10%		POST GRADUATE
3%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
28.	And, what is your total annual income? Just stop me when I read the correct catagory....</b><p><pre>
6%		LESS THAN $20,000
11%		$20,000-$29,000
16%		$30,000-$39,000
17%		$40,000-$49,000
14%		$50,000-$59,000
9%		$60,000-$69,000
11%		$70,000+
17%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
29.	Do you consider yourself to be a Democrat or Republican? </b><p><pre>
29%		STRONG DEMOCRAT
14%		WEAK DEMOCRAT
8%		INDEPENDENT LEANING DEMOCRAT
13%		STRONG INDEPENDENT
6%		INDEPENDENT LEANING REPUBLICAN	
8%		WEAK REPUBLICAN
13%		STRONG REPUBLICAN
10%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
30.	Thinking of your general outlook politically, would you describe yourself as conservative, somewhat conservative, moderate, somewhat liberal, or liberal?</b><p><pre>
23%		CONSERVATIVE
21%		SOMEWHAT CONSERVATIVE
32%		MODERATE
11%		SOMEWHAT LIBERAL
7%		LIBERAL
7%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
31.	Thinking back to 1992, and regardless of how you would vote today, did you support George Bush, Ross Perot, or Bill Clinton. If you were not registered or did not vote, just say so.</b><p><pre>
25%		GEORGE BUSH
14%		ROSS PEROT
48%		BILL CLINTON
5%		DID NOT VOTE
8%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
32.	And in the 1994 congressional elections, did you support the Republican candidate or Democratic candidate for Congress. If you were not registered or did not vote, just say so.</b><p><pre>
27%		REPUBLICAN
48%		DEMOCRAT
3%		INDEPENDENT
8%		DID NOT VOTE
14%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
33.	If the election for President were held today, would you support Bill Clinton, the Democrat, Bob Dole, the Republican, or Ross Perot, the Independent?</b><p><pre>
50%		BILL CLINTON, DEMOCRAT
20%		BOB DOLE, REPUBLICAN
11%		ROSS PEROT, INDEPENDENT
19%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
34.	What do you consider to be your main racial or ethnic heritage: white, African-American, Hispanic, Asian-American, native-American, or other?</b><p><pre>
85%		WHITE
4%		AFRICAN-AMERICAN
2%		HISPANIC
2%		NATIVE-AMERICAN
1%		ASIAN-AMERICAN
2%		OTHER
5%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
35.	Gender (BY OBSERVATION)</b><p><pre>
52%		MALE
48%		FEMALE
</pre><P><b>
36.	And have you seen any of the union sponsored political campaign ads that have been run against Republican members of Congress over the past six months or so?</b><p><pre>
26%		YES
66%		NO
9%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
37.	Finally, do you feel that this is a worthwhile way for the national labor union leaders to spend monthly union dues?</b><p><pre>
27%		YES
59%		NO
14%		DON'T KNOW/REFUSED
</pre><P><b>
