<html><head><title>AMERICANS FOR A BALANCED BUDGET</TITLE></head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<blockquote>
<img src="/abb/images/hdr-pr.gif">
<P>

<h3>AMERICAN FOR A BALANCED BUDGET<BR>
LAUNCHES NATIONWIDE CAMPAIGN<BR>
TO COUNTER AFL-CIO LIES<BR>
ABOUT CONGRESSWOMAN CUBIN<BR>
</H3></CENTER>
<BR><P>
<b>For Immediate Release<br>
Contact: Ben Magliano<br>
202-638-6124<br>
<p>
          February 2, 1996</B> -- Americans For a Balanced Budget has launched the fifth wave of its nationwide campaign to correct the 
distortions and lies being told about Medicare spending. The first radio spots began airing in 
Wyoming today.<p>

Washington Congresswoman has been targeted by the AFL-CIO 
and other liberal special interest groups due to her votes in favor of the balanced budget. 
Numerous television and radio advertisements funded by these groups have made the erroneous 
claim that Congresswoman Cubin voted to cut Medicare.<p>

Americans For a Balanced Budget has decided to answer this charge with the truth. The budget 
passed by congress and vetoed by President Clinton increases Medicare spending by 48%.<p>

&quot;Check with any major news organizations - The New York Times, The Washington Post, ABC 
News - Their reports all prove that the congressional plan increases Medicare spending, &quot; says 
Tony Zagotta, President of Americans For a Balanced Budget, &quot;These lies and distortions are 
designed to divert our attention away from President Clinton and his unwillingness to propose 
his own seven year balanced budget .&quot;<p>

Americans For a Balanced Budget is one of the leading groups fighting for a balanced federal 
budget. Founded in 1990, the non-partisan grassroots organization has over 200,000 members in 
all fifty states.<p>


-30-

