<HEAD>
<TITLE>IN PRINT...a partial list of CRC's Publications</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/crc/images/bg.gif">
<a href="/crc/images/sidebar.map"><img src="/crc/images/sidebar.gif" alt="Navigation Bar" border="0" align="left" ISMAP></a>
<ul>
<h2>IN PRINT...a partial list of CRC's most recent publications</h2>
</B>(prices include postage; for more information call 202-393-2600; to order publications which do not appear on the website, send check or money order for the indicated amount to CRC, 727 15th Street N.W., Suite 800, Washington, D.C., 20005.)
<P>
<a href="/crc/about/buy.html.cgi">Purchase publications on-line</a><p>
<small>
<a href="#books">Books</a>
<br><a href="#occasionals">Occasionals</a>
<br><a href="#caprep">Capital Report</a>
<br><a href="#newsletters">Newsletters</a>
<br><a href="#profiles">Profiles</a>
</small>
<P><br>
<a name="books"></a>
<font size="2">
<B>* <a href="/crc/books">BOOKS</a> *</b><br>
<small>(links in this section lead to summaries and ordering information)</small>
<P>
<ul>
<b>Studies in Organization Trends
</B>
<P>
<I><a href="/crc/books/elderly.html">Frightening America's Elderly: How The Age Lobby Holds Seniors Captive</a></I>, by Thomas J. DiLorenzo; Preface by Senator Alan Simpson, 1996, 108pp. indexed, $15.00 [item SOT10] (rates for multiple copies available)
<P>
<I><a href="/crc/books/green.html">Environmentalism at the Crossroads: Green Activism in America</a></I>, by Jonathan H. Adler; Preface by John Stossel, 1995, 299 pp., $30.00 [item SOT09]  (rates for multiple copies available)
<P>
<I><a href="/crc/books/nanny.html">The Rise of the Nanny State: How Consumer Advocates Try to Run Our Lives</a></I>, by Tom Holt, 1995, 134 pp., $20.00  [item SOT08]  (rates for multiple copies available)
<P>
<I>Animal Rights: Executive Summary</I>, by Daniel T. Oliver, 1993, 7 pp. [item SOT07A]
<P>

<B>Studies in Philanthropy</B>
<P><I>Patterns of Corporate Philanthropy IX: Giving in the Clinton Era</I>, by Austin Fulk &amp; Stuart Nolan; Preface by Robert H. Malott, 1996, 193 pp., $25.00 [item SIP20]
<P>
<I><a href="/crc/books/neighbor.html">Loving Your Neighbor: A Principled Guide To Personal Charity</a></I>, edited by Marvin Olasky, 1995, 146 pp., $15.00 [item SIP19]<I> </I>(rates for multiple copies available)
<P> 
<I><a href="/crc/books/pdi.html">The Great Philanthropists &amp; the Problem of &quot;Donor Intent</a>&quot;</I>, by Martin Morse Wooster, 1994, 158 pp., $25.00 [item SIP18] (rates for multiple copies available) 
<P>
<I><a href="/crc/patterns">Patterns of Corporate Philanthropy VIII: Public Affairs Giving and the Forbes 250</a></I>, by Stuart Nolan; Preface by Malcolm S. Forbes, Jr., 1994, 182 pp., $25.00  [item SIP17]
<P>
<I>Hidden Politics: &quot;Progressive&quot; Nonprofits Target the States</I>, by Thomas J. DiLorenzo, edited by Dan T. Oliver, 1993, 78 pp., $20.00 [item SIP16]
<P>
<I>Patterns of Corporate Philanthropy VII: Executive Hypocrisy</I>, <I>Executive Summary</I>, by Stuart Nolan and Gregory P. Conko; Summary Essay by Dr. M. Bruce Johnson; Preface by Dr. Richard W. Rahn, 1993, 64 pp., $5.00 [item SIP15A]
<P>
