<html><head>
<title>Civil Rights Resource Center</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<center>

<hr noshade>

<P>

The Claremont Institute is in the process of building a Civil Rights Resource Center for World Wide Web users. This center will include Institute policy briefings as well as an extensive, interactive database which will include journal articles, facts, figures, polling data, and other information related to civil rights, affirmative action, and racial preferences.

<P>

<hr noshade>

<P>

<ul>

<a href="pubop.htm">Equal Rights and Public Opinion</a>: A Special Report  


<P>
<a href="postccri.htm">Lessons of the Affirmative Action Campaign</a><br> <i>by Larry P. Arnn</i><p>
<a href="victim.html">Equal Opportunities Denied</a><br> <i>by Tom McClintock and Steven McCarthy</i><p>
<a href="citguide.html">A Citizen's Guide to the Affirmative Action</a><br> <i>by Douglas A. Jeffrey and Brian T. Kennedy</i><p>
<a href="fairness.html">America's Passion for Fairness</a><br> <i>by Larry P. Arnn</i><p>
<a href="trainwrk.html">The Affirmative Action Trainwreck</a><br> <i>by Edward J. Erler</i><p>

