<HEAD>
<TITLE>FREE Mission Statement</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" BACKGROUND="/free/Images/bluewhite_paper.gif"><IMG SRC = "/free/Images/flogo.gif" ALT = "">
<H1><B>FREE's Mission Statement</B></H1>
<P>FREE is a research and educational foundation.  Its purpose is to advance conservation and environmental values consistent with individual freedom and responsibility.  We develop and advocate environmental policies whose goals are realized through private property rights, market incentives, and voluntary organizations.  </P>
<P>Free works with leaders in universities, businesses, environmental groups, government, the media, and think-tanks.  We conduct seminars and conferences, sponsor and write books and articles, and organize special issues of magazines.  </P>
<P>Our most valuable contributions to public policy and the economy come from our incentive-based, free-enterprise alternatives to the policies of the collective environmentalists.  FREE works with a substantial number of academics and writers who hold principled commitments to the ideals of America's Founding Fathers.  These individuals have earned the respect of the policy community for their intellectual integrity and independence.</P>
<P>Essentially, FREE provides an organized forum for developing and debating approaches to ecological issues consistent with the classical liberal values of free enterprise and individual responsibility.  FREE analyses proposals of environmentalists who reject markets and incentives in favor of a bureaucratic, command-and-control approach.  Many professional policy analysts agree that we have earned the intellectual high ground.</P>
<P>Now that all politicians claim to be environmentalists, and the &quot;green&quot; movement is picking up great momentum, their is huge potential for mischief.  Environmental quality can be harmonized with a society of free and responsible individuals.  FREE shows how these goals can go together.  At this time, support for FREE's work is an especially important investment in the public policy arena.</P>  <!--FOOT--><HR>
<BR><NOBR><A HREF="/free/"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/Home.gif" ALT="FREE Home Page"></A><A HREF="/free/FREE.archive.html"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/Pub.gif" ALT="FREE Online Archives"></A><A HREF="/free/FP/FREE.perspectives.html"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/FP.gif" ALT="FREE Perspectives"></A></NOBR><BR><NOBR><A HREF="/free/ST96/FJ96.ST1996.html"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/Col.gif" ALT="Latest Column"></A><A HREF="/free/FREE.archive.html"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/Search.gif" ALT="Search FREE Web Site"></A><A HREF="/free/FREE.contact.html"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/Contact.gif" ALT="Contact FREE"></A>
