<TITLE>FREE's Activities</TITLE>
<META name="description" content="FREE Activities">
<META name="keywords" content="FREE, Activities, Publications, Gallatin, Columns, Seminars, Books, Managing the Commons, Environmental Gore">
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" BACKGROUND="/free/Images/bluewhite_paper.gif"><IMG SRC = "/free/Images/flogo.gif" ALT = ""><P><H1>FREE'S ACTIVITIES</H1></P><H3><P>FREE's 1995 PROGRAM OUTLINE</P></H3>

<OL>
<LI><P>  <A HREF="ST95/FREE.ST1995.html">Op-Ed &amp; Syndicated Columns</A>:  Regular bi-monthly columns appeared through Knight-Ridder syndication in the Seattle Times  with, occasional special columns in <CITE>Rocky Mountain News, New York Times, Wall Street Journal</CITE>. </P>
<LI><P>  Regional National Public Radio programs:  &quot;Toward a New Shade of Green&quot;</P>
<LI><P>  Federal Judges Seminar Series:  The first 1995 seminar, <CITE>Environmental Economics &amp; Policy Analysis, A Seminar For Federal Judges</CITE> was held June 10-15 at the Diamond J Ranch near Ennis, Montana.  The second (same title),was held September 12-17 at the Elk Horn Ranch, Big Sky, Montana.</P>
<LI><P>  Writers Program on Culture, Values and Environmental Protection:   FREE hosted, <CITE>Liberty, Responsibility, and the Question of  Environment</CITE> a program for environmental writers June 29-July 2 at the Gallatin Gateway Inn, Bozeman, Montana.  We also held approximately 12 smaller meetings with writers.  This project culminated in the creation of the <A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/gallatin">Gallatin Institute</A>, a sister organization to FREE but one focused upon transmitters of culture rather than economists and policy analysts.</P>
</OL>
<P>
<H3><P> 1996 CONFIRMED PROGRAMS</P></H3>

<OL>
<LI><P>  <A HREF="ST96/FREE.ST1996.html">Op-Ed &amp; Syndicated Columns</A>:  Columns originating in the <CITE>Seattle Times</CITE> and syndicated through Knight-Ridder will continue.  Recent columns include:</P>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ST96/Primer1.ST1996.html">Avoid Political Extinction with A New Shade of Green</A>
<LI><A HREF="ST96/Primer2.ST1996.html">Clinton's 'Green Decrees':  Easy Answers Postpone Reform</A>
<LI><A HREF="ST96/Press.ST1996.html">Environmentalism Needs A Free Press</A>
<LI><A HREF="ST96/Speech.ST1996.html">A Green Campaign Speech for a Better Environment</A>
<LI><A HREF="ST96/FishDem.ST1996.html">Democracies Don't Fight-- Unless It's Over Fish</A></UL>

<LI><P>  <A HREF="gopher://gopher.npr.org:70/11/NPR_Online">National Public Radio</A> programs are underway.  &quot;Toward a New Shade of Green&quot; airs immediately before the National Public Radio program &quot;Living on Earth&quot;.</P>
<LI><P>  1996 Federal Judges Program:  FREE has scheduled three federal judges seminars to be held in Montana in 1996.  The theme for the June 15-20 and September 17-22 seminars is <CITE>Environmental Economics and Policy Analysis for Federal Judges</CITE>.  Our new program, <CITE>Bringing Sound Science &amp; Economics to Risk Analysis</CITE> will be offered August 21-25.</P>

<LI><P>  Writers Programs:   Two programs are scheduled.  <UL><LI><P>The first, sponsored by the Liberty Fund, &quot;I'll Take My Stand (On the Range)&quot; is scheduled for July 18-21 at the Gallatin Gateway Inn, Bozeman, Montana.</P>  <LI>The second program, &quot;Second Thoughts on Culture and Ecology: Introductory Perspectives&quot;, is scheduled October 10-13, also at the Gallatin Gateway Inn.</P>  <P>FREE provides important support for these <A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/gallatin">Gallatin Institute</A> programs.</P>

<LI><P>  FREE's &quot;Rolling Salon&quot;:   From Anaconda to Dillon, MT.</P>
</P><IMG SRC="/free/Images/van.gif"><IMG SRC="/free/Images/biker.gif"></UL>
</OL>
