You are at it again, Leslie, another batch of bat guano. Don't you even have a clue about reality? The reason we don't like the Brady Bill is that it does absolutely zero to prevent crime, and is nothing more than something to make liberals feel good. To correct you, voters, liberal, conservative or whatever, may vote any way they choose. Judges are mandated by the Constitution not to have individual agendas; voters vote as such; liberal judges do not. And then, Leslie, you pull the expected liberal ruse: switch the subject to homosexuals, lesbians, minorities and women's bodies. It sure takes the mental work out of the discussion, doesn't it? Maybe <I>NR</I> will have the courage to make a Soapbox of your obsessions for us to comment on.<br> 
