<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/16sept96/inprint.html">September 16, 1996</a> See Jack Grow: <B>Richard  Brookhiser</B> notes that although Jack Kemp may have revitalized the Dole campaign, he may also be tough to handle.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/02sept96/inprint.html">September 2, 1996</a> Rolling Back Quotas: <B>Rich  Lowry</B> introduces Ward Connerly, the prime mover behind the California Civil Rights Initiative.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/12aug96/inprint.html">August 12,1996</a> Jumping Ship: <B>Rich  Lowry</B> on the disheartening effect the Dole campaign is having on Congressional Republicans.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/29july96/inprint.html">July 29, 1996</a> See How They Run: <B>Rich  Lowry</B> on Bob Dole's potential running mates.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/15july96/inprint.html">July 15, 1996</a> Capital Offense: <B>John Dizard</B> on the decline and fall of Washington, D.C.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/01july96/contents.html">July 1, 1996</a> Is the War on Drugs Really Lost?  400 Readers Respond with a reply by <B>Wm. F. Buckley, Jr</B>.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/17june96/contents.html">June 17, 1996</a> Rude Awakening: <b>David Satter</b> on the revival of Russia's Communists.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/03june96/contents.html">June 3, 1996</a> The Unnecessary GOP Meltdown: <b>Kate O'Beirne</b> and <b>Ramesh Ponnuru</b> on Republican skittishness.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/20may96/contents.html">May 20, 1996</a> Crossroads: <b>Lawrence Kudlow</b> examines the confluence of politcs and the market.
<P>
<LI><a href="/nationalreview/06may96/contents.html">May 6, 1996</a> Reagan's Spoiled Children: <b>Ramesh Ponnuru</b> sees the future of the conservative movement threatened by infighting.
