<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Small Business Survival Coalition</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<img src="/sbsc/sbsmall.gif">
<p>
<P>
<center>
<h2>
  Small Business Survival Coalition<BR>
</h2>
</center>
<P>
<blockquote>
Over the past two years, the Small Business Survival Committee
(SBSC) has heard from scores of business organizations nationwide
that a more effective influence in Washington is needed to reverse
laws that hurt free enterprise.  Feeling isolated and disenfranchised
from Washington, state and local business organizations have long
known that inside-the-beltway antics will do little to stop the
growing intrusiveness of government.<BR>
<P>
The Small Business Survival (SBS) Coalition utilizes the grassroots
strengths of state and local organizations to mobilize its business
membership and leaders. <BR>
<P>
 If hundreds of business organizations nationwide speak with one
voice when key legislation or policy is being proposed, debated
or considered, powerful special interest forces who support the
status quo of big government can be overcome.  If the status quo
is left unchallenged, common sense advocates will be drowned out.
<BR>
<P>
<a href="/sbsc/coalition/sbscapp.html">Join the Small Business Survival Coalition</a>.
<P>
<a href="/sbsc/coalition/sbsc4.html">Membership Rates.</a>
<p>
<a href="/sbsc/coalition/sbsc2.html">SBS Coaltion Program Benefits and More Information</a>
<P>
If you have questions, please direct them to <a href="mailto:rstikes@sbsc.org">rstikes@sbsc.org</a>
<BR>
</blockquote>
<BR>
<p>
<center>
| <a href="/sbsc/">Home</a> |</center>
