<html>
<title>Unleashing America's Potential -- Foreword -- TRC</title>
<body><center><img src="/taxcom/fr-head.gif" alt="TRC:  Unleashing America's Potential"><br><font size="-1"><a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> | <a href="mailto:arnettgm@heritage.org">Feedback</a> | <a href="/townhall/">Town Hall</a></font><P></center>
<center>
<h2>UNLEASHING AMERICA'S POTENTIAL:</h2>
<b>A pro-growth, pro-family tax system for the 21st century</b>
<P>
Report of the National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform<br>
JANUARY 1996
</center><P>
<blockquote>
Download options:
<ul> 
<li>Self-extracting PKZip <a href="/taxcom/trc-wp.exe">WordPerfect 5.1 for DOS</a> full-text version (144,910 bytes)
<li><a href="/taxcom/trc.mcw">Word 4.0 for Mac</a> (not compressed) full-text version (258,000 bytes)
<li>You can view the entire document on-line, using the following Table of Contents to get you started.
</ul>

<center>
<h3><font size="+3">T</font>able of <font size="+3">C</font>ontents</h3>
</center>

<a href="/taxcom/repfor.html">Foreword</a> by  <I>Senate Leader Dole and Speaker Gingrich</I><br> 
<a href="/taxcom/reppre.html">Preface</a> by <I>Edwin J. Feulner</I><br> 
<a href="/taxcom/repintro.html">Introduction</a> by  <I>Jack Kemp</I><br>
<a href="/taxcom/repimag.html">Imagine an America...</a> <br>
<a href="/taxcom/repboil.html">At the Boiling Point</a> <br>
<a href="/taxcom/repwork.html">Working Principles</a><br>
<a href="/taxcom/repnew.html">A New Tax System for the 21st Century</a> - <b>"Commission Recommendations"</b><br>
<a href="/taxcom/repbios.html">Biographies and Appreciation</a><br>
<a href="/taxcom/reptest.html">The &quot;Tax Test&quot;</a><br>
</blockquote>
<center>
<h3>Discussion and Background Papers</h3>
</center>
<blockquote>
<a href="/taxcom/mitch1.html">Historical Lessons for Tax Reform</a> by Dan Mitchell (Heritage Foundation)<br>
<a href="/taxcom/mitch2.html">Benefits of a Single Tax Rate System</a> by Dan Mitchell<br>
<a href="/taxcom/bart1.html">Taxes on the Poor</a> by Bruce Bartlett (National Center for Policy Analysis)<br>
<a href="/taxcom/moore1.html">Why Capital Matters</a> by Stephen Moore (CATO Institue)<br>
<a href="/taxcom/reyn1.html">Estimates vs. Reality</a> by Alan Reynolds<br>
<a href="/taxcom/ent1.html">Tax Biases Against Saving and Investment and How to Fix Them</a> by Stephen Entin (Institute for Research on the Economics of Taxation)<br>
<a href="/taxcom/ent2.html">Growth-Friendly Tax Systems</a> by Stephen Entin<br>
<a href="/taxcom/reyn2.html">Deductions and Tradeoffs</a> by Alan Reynolds<br>
<a href="/taxcom/ent3.html">Income Tax Treatment of Payroll Taxes and Social Security Benefits</a> by Stephen Entin<br>
<a href="/taxcom/ent4.html">Simplify International Taxation</a> by Stephen Entin<P>

These briefing papers were prepared by economic consultants and commission staff to assist in the deliberations of the National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform.  They are made available because they contain information that provides more detail on some of the concepts and issues that were considered by the commission.  For more information, please contact the authors.  Contact information is listed at the end of each paper.
</blockquote>
<P><center><font size="-1"><a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> | <a href="mailto:arnettgm@heritage.org">Feedback</a> | <a href="/taxcom/ .html">Next Section</a><br><a href="/townhall/">Town Hall</a></font><P>&#169 Copyright National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform 1996</center>
</html>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT16-B28-107</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA022-000232-B033-84</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.savers.org:80/taxcom/charge.html 204.71.237.73 19970107231923 text/html 2375
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Tuesday, 07-Jan-97 23:19:24 GMT
Last-modified: Friday, 12-Jan-96 21:51:18 GMT
Content-length: 2191
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head>
<title>TRC - Mission Statement</title>
</head>
<body>
<img src="/taxcom/logo.gif" alt="TRC" align="left">
<center>
<font size="-1"><a href="/taxcom/backgrnd.html">Background</a> | <a href="/taxcom/facts.html">Facts Sheet</a></font>
<P>
<br>
<P>
<h2>Mission Statement</h2>
<hr>
</center>
<P>
<blockquote>
<br>
<p>
The current tax code -- with its high marginal tax rates and thousands of pages of rules, 
regulations, and red tape -- poses a formidable barrier to economic growth. 
<p>
<ul>
<li>It punishes the most dynamic forces for growth in our economy -- the small business owners 
and entrepreneurs who turn bold ideas into new businesses, new jobs, and new products.
<p> 
<li>It discourages working Americans who are trying to save for the future to build a better life 
for themselves and their families.
 <p>
<li>It is endlessly complex and confusing, costing literally billions of dollars in lost time and 
effort.
</ul>
<p>
Tax reform must move toward making the tax code more family friendly and create incentives 
for savings and investment.    
<p>
The congressional leadership has <a href="/taxcom/dole.html">asked</a> the National Commission on Economic Growth and 
Tax Reform to start with a blank piece of paper and design a system that is flatter, fairer, and 
simpler -- one that will encourage strong economic growth and greater opportunity for all.
<p>
The commission will gather the views of American citizens from all walks of life and will 
gather the best  available analysis and evidence from the experts who study and analyze tax 
policy.  The commission is expected to issue its recommendations and its report in December.  
<p>
The commission’s report should provide recommendations that will contribute to 
reinvigorating entrepreneurship, risk-taking, savings, investment, and work efforts.  Its goal is 
to produce a report that will make America more competitive and expand the nation’s 
worldwide leadership in the twenty-first century global economy.
</blockquote>
<p>
<center>
[ <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> | <a href="/taxcom/backgrnd.html">More TRC Background</a> ]
</center>
</body>
</html>


